Articles.Content: Please upload output_log.txt from your crash folder and not error.txt

I'm not certain, but from your description and the looks of that error log, I would say that's an out-of-memory error. That is, the game has reached the 32 bit memory cap of 4GB RAM usage. If that is the case, you can either wait for KSP 1.1 to be released or remove some mods or stock parts. EVE uses an enormous amount of RAM, so could texture replacer, depending on how many textures you're replacing. Is AVG that addon version checker thing? That should use next to no RAM. The others would use a moderate amount but nowhere near as much as EVE or KSP itself.

EDIT: If your computer has more than 4GB of RAM available, you could also try the [thread=117224]Windows 64 bit community hack[/thread] but it can be buggy. Squad withdrew the windows 64 bit version for a reason, but I hear it's a lot better than it used to be. Don't expect any help from Squad or any modders if you use that though, as it's not officially supported.

Edited September 2, 2015 by TheMoonRover
